From c4e71f4698dd509ceeeefd19b7ba696edcc3e9f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 16 Nov 2025 10:32:20 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd:Handle address translation for FT
 in assoc response

When the AP sends a response for a reassoc/assoc request in Fast
Transition (FT), the link address is incorrectly overwritten by
the station's MLD address if the station is found in the FT roaming
list. This prevents the station from receiving the assoc response.
Remove the address reassignment so that the reassoc/assoc response
is sent to the station's link address.

Fixes: I3e66cbd27c1(UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Support MLD STA
reconnection on same band)
Patch-dependency: s021-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Support-MLD-STA-reconnecti.patch

Signed-off-by: Sowmiya Sree Elavalagan <ssreeela@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/ieee802_11.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
index 91d5bf7..8b497f3 100644
--- a/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
+++ b/src/ap/ieee802_11.c
@@ -6374,8 +6374,6 @@ static void handle_assoc(struct hostapd_data *hapd,
 			wpa_printf(MSG_DEBUG,
 				   "FT over DS: Check for STA entry with ML address");
 			sta = get_sta_from_ft_ds_list(hapd, mgmt, len, reassoc);
-			if (sta)
-				sa = sta->addr;
 		}
 	}
 
-- 
